I was the music director for my first Award Show this past weekend. It just so happened to be the @naacpimageawards Ceremony & Dinner where I also performed. The amount of work that goes in to a production like this is ridiculous! I learned a lot, but I also realized what was already in me! As I toured the US on my #JAMOTour to support my third solo album, my daytime was filled with music curation, emails, zooms, production questions and the infamous “Run Of Show”. The Stretch was real, but I’m thankful for it and I can’t wait to do it again. Sending love to the amazing group of geniuses that helped me make the ceremony a success! They showed up to Rehearsal playing and singing the Hell out of all the music. Thank Y’all for your gifts and time! Im looking forward to the next!

Let me Keep it 💯 with y’all. Not everyone tells the story behind the highlight reel..

It was November of 2022, when I turned down just about every phone call to tour as a drummer with other artist. This decision made the beginning of 2023 rocky for a multitude of reasons. I was nervous, uncomfortable, and full of questions about how it all would work out. In spite of my feelings, I made the jump! I Jumped in and focused on the vision, sound, and concept that only God could give to me. 

The year started off soooo dry; and I mean Dryyy y’all! The calendar was extremely light!!🤣🤦🏽‍♂️
Logically, it made NO SENSE! All I could think about was the amount of tour dates I declined and the fact that my wife I had just bought a new home; Crazy!🤦🏽‍♂️ The only thing on the books was a promo tour for my album, “Jamo” that was going to cost me money ( Shout out to the independent artist out there💪🏽✊🏽). 

I made many attempts to hold on to tours and numerous opportunities as a sideman, but I knew deep down in my soul that it was time. It was time to Jump.

Still reluctant about declining tours, I started to prepare for the first leg of the “JAMO” tour ( it was the only thing on my schedule.... literally 😂). I will never forget the first show day In New Orleans. We had just finished 4 days of rehearsal and I received a call from my team about an inquiry for us to come to DC. I smiled and a sudden peace came over me before we took the stage that night. As the tour continued, the phone kept ringing and the year began to shape up faster than I could have ever imagined. 

Looking back at 2023, I would jump all over again. Building a career of your own that doesn’t depend on anyone else is totally worth it! 🙏🏽 Even though I was afraid of the outcome, I leaned in to what was unfamiliar. As uncomfortable as the little drummer boy in me was to start the year, my decision created space for me to be fully present while working a vision that will forever expand my path.

Thank You, 2023! Let’s Go 2024! I’m Ready for you now.🙌🏽
